{"auto_collapse":false,"body":{"cells_cell_type":["code","code","code","code","code","code","code","code"],"cells_execution_count":["null","null","null","null","null","null","null","null"],"cells_source":["!pip install assemblyline-client==4.0.0b11","import pandas as pd
","#from tqdm import tqdm
","from tqdm.notebook import tqdm
","from assemblyline_client import get_client
","import time as time
","import json
","from pathlib import Path
","import threading","def recieve_thread(df):
","    #sidsDelete = []
","    # First read all the messages off the queue
","    msgs = al_client.ingest.get_message_list('queue')
","    # Debug print the msgs
","    #pp.pprint(msgs)
","    # Return if queue is empty sleep for a few seconds before returning
","    if (len(msgs) == 0):
","        time.sleep(3)
","        return(df)
","    
","    for msg in msgs:
","        
","        # First I need to find the entry in the df
","        index = df.loc[df["File Name"] == msg['submission']['files'][0]['name']].index
","        # Update the df with the sid and score
","        df.loc[index, 'sid']  = msg['submission']['sid']
","        df.loc[index, 'score']  = msg['score']
","        
","        # Then query for the status using the sid and catch exceptions if it doesn't exist
","        try:
","            sid_status = al_client.submission.is_completed(msg['submission']['sid'])
","        
","        #except ClientError:
","        except:
","            #print("Error: ", sid_status)
","            df.loc[index, 'state'] = 'error' 
","            continue
","        
","        # When it exists then pull all the info
","        if (sid_status == True):
","            
","            #sidsDelete.append(msg['submission']['sid'])
","            # Getting the 'sid'
","            #print("Getting the SID: ", msg['submission']['sid'])
","            # If it has been processed, then pull the result
","            try:
","                submission_details=al_client.submission.full(msg['submission']['sid'])
","        
","        
","            except:
","                #print("Error: ", sid_status)
","                df.loc[index, 'state'] = 'error' 
","                continue
","            
","            # Then update the state in the df:
","            df.loc[index, 'state']=submission_details['state']
","            
","            # Use the Result Path to create the file handle
","            #print("index = ", index)
","            #print("Result Path :", df['Result Path'].values[index])
","            #print("File Name :", df['File Name'].values[index])
","            #Full_Path=df.loc[index, 'Result Path']+'/'+df.loc[index, 'File Name']+".json"
","            #Full_Path=str(df['Result Path'].values[index]+'/'+df['File Name'].values[index]+".json")
","            Full_Path=df['Result Path'].values[index]+'/'+df['File Name'].values[index]+".json"
","            print("Writing Full Path = ", Full_Path)
","            #print(type(Full_Path))
","            
","            
","            # And write out the results in a json file
","            j = json.dumps(submission_details['results'], indent=4)
","            #f = open(submission_details['files'][0]['name']+".json", 'w')
","            f = open(Path(Full_Path[0]), 'w')
","            print(j, file=f)
","            f.close()
","            
","            # Final update to  the state in the df:
","            df.loc[index, 'state']='written'
","            
","            # Finally delete the submission ta have space on the AL instance
","            #print("Deleting: ", msg['submission']['sid'])
","            # Then query for the status using the sid and catch exceptions if it doesn't exist
","            #try:
","            #    result=al_client.submission.delete(msg['submission']['sid'])
","        
","        
","            #except:
","            #    #print("Error: ", sid_status)
","            #    df.loc[index, 'state'] = 'error' 
","            #    continue
","            
","            
","            
","        else:
","            
","            # Else its still being processed, we'll have to remember to deal with the cleanup afterward
","            # Let's update the status to submitted
","            df.loc[index, 'state']='submitted'
","        
","    # Finally go through the submitted and completed sids and delete them to conserve resources
","    # Catch errors and just continue
","    
","    # Maybe its easier to set the xpire time on submissions to 3 days, so AL can then delete the submission itself
","    #for sid in sidsDelete:
","    #    print("deleting sid: ", sid)
","    #    try:
","    #         al_client.submission.delete(sid)
","    #    except:
","    #         continue
","                
","     
","    return df","train_df=pd.read_csv("train_df_processed.csv",index_col=0)","al_client = get_client("https://localhost:443", auth=('admin', 'admin'), verify=False)
","while True:
